I assume the StateString property is not writable through the public 
interface of the MBean class?

If it /is/ writable, then your test should impersonate JBoss and set it.

If it is /not/ writable, then consider using the &quot;subclass to test&quot; 
technique.

public void testDoNotInitializeIfServiceNotStarted() throws Exception {
     MyMBean mbean = new MyMBean() {
         protected String getStateString() {
             return &quot;Stopped&quot;;    // Something other than &quot;Started&quot;
         }
     };

     mbean.initLocation();
     // assert mbean didn&#39;t change to &quot;Started&quot; state...
}

Something like that.
